Sec. 148.024. DELAY IN COLLECTION OF PAYMENT INSTRUMENTS. An
instrument issued in payment for livestock under this subchapter
shall be drawn on banks that are so located as not to artificially
delay collection of funds through mail or otherwise cause an undue
lapse of time in the clearance process.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1387, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

